This will not work as webpack only sets `NODE_ENV` during the build. If you want this to be set when the config is loaded, you need to set it when launching the build in the command line. But, the best option for you is to turn the config into a function

```
const config = mode =&gt; ({
  entry: &#39;./src/entry.js&#39;,
  output: {
    filename: &#39;script.js&#39;,
  },
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.(png|svg|jpg|jpeg|webp)$/,
        use: [
